Package suncertify.presentation

Contains the graphical user interfaces that allow the user(s) to configurate the remote server, the local non-distributed client and the networked distributed client.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClientFrame
    Shows the database data in a graphical user interface, and has the functionality required by the requested use cases (search and book a client).
    DBTableModel
    Concrete implementation of javax.swing.table.AbstractTableModel, suited to the database schema of the database file.
    LocalClientFrame
    Implements the local client fine-grained functionality, called by the parent class "template methods".
    NetworkedConfigFrame
    Graphical user interface window that allows remote, distributed users, to configure the host and port of the target machine, where the remote server is hosted.
    PropertyManager
    Manages key-value properties in memory, saves them to a file, and recovers them from the file.
    RemoteClientFrame
    Implements the remote distributed client fine-grained functionality, called by the parent class "template methods".
    ServerConfigFrame
    Graphical user interface window that allows a user to run a setup configuration for a remote distributed database server.
    ServerFrame
    Graphical user interface window that displays the status of the running remote database server.
    StandaloneConfigFrame
    Graphical user interface window that allows local non-distributed users, to configure the location in the file system where the database file resides.

Package suncertify.presentation Description

Contains the graphical user interfaces that allow the user(s) to configurate the remote server, the local non-distributed client and the networked distributed client. Moreover, it contains the parent class that shows the database data and has "template methods" that calls on fine-grained operations that are implemented by child classes, whether the operation is local or network distributed.
